<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><!DOCTYPE topic  PUBLIC '-//OASIS//DTD DITA Topic//EN'  'topic.dtd'><topic id="GUID_FF127B40-1B74-40D6-ACBE-731F2B887A2A"><title>PCIe Gen2 M.2 Topology</title><body><section id="SECTION_B7F95F6C-4C4F-4761-BC16-75FFDE8AE4DE"><fig id="FIG_pcie_gen2_m_2_topology_diagram_1"><title>PCIe Gen2 M.2 Topology Diagram</title><image href="FIG_pcie gen2 m.2 topology diagram_1.png" scalefit="yes" id="IMG_pcie_gen2_m_2_topology_diagram_1_png" /></fig><table id="TABLE_B7F95F6C-4C4F-4761-BC16-75FFDE8AE4DE_1"><title>PCIe Gen2 M.2 Topology Notes</title><tgroup cols="2"><thead><row><entry>Note</entry><entry>Detail</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry><p>Add-in-card (M4 + M5)</p></entry><entry><p>The total length of the add-in card (M4 + M5) is usually 38 mm to 50.4 mm.</p><p>The M4 + M5 segment is a combination of MS/ SL/ DSL (MS where required to connect to surface mounted components).</p><p>The M4 + M5 segment has a typical via count of 1.</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>AC capacitor value</p></entry><entry><p>Gen2: 75 nF - 265 nF</p><p>Gen2 nominal = 100 nF</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>Breakout length and spacing</p></entry><entry><p>An initial breakout segment of 4 mm in length with a tighter pair-to-pair spacing of 0.11 mm - 0.16 mm  is allowed. </p><p>The total breakout length is still 15.2 mm.</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>Routing type for mainstream stackup</p></entry><entry><p>Prefer non-interleaved routes in different layers.</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><table id="TABLE_B7F95F6C-4C4F-4761-BC16-75FFDE8AE4DE_2"><title>Max Number of vias</title><tgroup cols="4"><thead><row><entry>Signal Group</entry><entry>Max Number of Vias Allowed</entry><entry>Via Placement</entry><entry>Notes</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry><p>Rx, Tx</p></entry><entry><p>4</p></entry><entry><p>Total Channel</p></entry><entry><p>GEN2 (not counting microvia under package).</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>Rx, Tx</p></entry><entry><p>1</p></entry><entry><p>Post-Channel</p></entry><entry><p>Express card/M.2/Add-in card</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="SECTION_271A0F24-3D36-4924-A535-5F783E6BC549"><title>Mainstream, Rx,Tx</title><table id="TABLE_271A0F24-3D36-4924-A535-5F783E6BC549_1"><title>PCIe Gen2 M.2 Topology Mainstream, Rx,Tx Routing Guidelines</title><tgroup cols="4"><thead><row><entry>Segment</entry><entry>Tline Type</entry><entry>Max Length Segment (mm)</entry><entry>Max Length Segment Note</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry><p>BO</p></entry><entry><p>DSL, MS, SL</p></entry><entry><p>15.2</p></entry><entry><p /></entry></row><row><entry><p>M1 + M2</p></entry><entry><p>DSL, MS, SL</p></entry><entry><p /></entry><entry><p>Max length is BO+M1+M2+M3 &lt; 229 mm</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>M3</p></entry><entry><p>MS</p></entry><entry><p>8</p></entry><entry><p /></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><p>Max Length Total (mm): 229</p><p>Max Length Total Note: Max length is BO+M1+M2+M3 &lt; 229 mm</p></section></body></topic>